description.@value: The five poems making up the Khamsah by Niẓāmī Ganjavī (1140 or 41-1202 or 3), containing 19 whole-page miniatures, one (f. 41r) contemporary; 14 in the Herat later-Timurid style; and four (ff 234v, 245v, 250v and 271v) in the Tabriz/Safavid style of c. 1535-40. Three paintings ( ff. 121v, 161r and 231v) are attributed to Bihzad. Consists of: Add MS 25900, ff 5v-30v: Makhzan al-asrār Add MS 25900, ff 31v-100v: Khusraw u ShīrīnAdd MS 25900, ff 101v-150v: Laylā u MajnūnAdd MS 25900, ff 151v-205r: Haft paykarAdd MS 25900, ff 206v-319v: Iskandarnāmah
